<h3 id="sorting-each-line">Sorting Each Line</h3>
<p>Whether thereâ€™s one line or two, once we know which line each character belongs to, we sort the line in ascending order of x-coordinates. Assuming thereâ€™s one, we now have the transcribed number plate! If thereâ€™s two, we sort the first line. Then, we sort the second line. Finally, we append the sorted detections from the second line to the sorted detections from the first line. You can write your own script to automate this and output this information into a more useful format such as a CSV file. Given <a href="/">here</a> (Yet to be uploaded) is the modified driver program.</p>

